# Algorithm Summary

## Algorithm for action recognition 

### 1. 3D convolution 
#### Essay (The logic figure could be refered and easily been understood.)
http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.442.8617&rep=rep1&type=pdf
####  Theory Intro
https://towardsdatascience.com/step-by-step-implementation-3d-convolutional-neural-network-in-keras-12efbdd7b130
https://www.kaggle.com/shivamb/3d-convolutions-understanding-use-case
#### code
https://github.com/facebookarchive/C3D.git

### 2. iDT (Improved Dense Trajectories)
#### Essay
https://openaccess.thecvf.com/content_iccv_2013/papers/Wang_Action_Recognition_with_2013_ICCV_paper.pdf
#### code
https://github.com/chuckcho/iDT.git
#### ps:
'''Currently, the deep learning has surpassed the iDT algorithm for action detecting. But the iDT always could improve the final result after deep learning. 
Therefore, most of papers with better results are in the form of "Our method+iDT" in recent years.'''

